grade_evaluation.et:
Maximum 100 points can be received. 
The grade consists of several group-works, presentations and individual assignments:
Phase 1 (5%, 5 points): overview of the planning area & aim and vision of the plan (group assessment), analysis of spatial mobility plans  (individual assessment), individual contribution (pass/fail, individual assessment)
Phase 2 (45%, 45 points): empirical study (30 points, group assessment), individual conversation (15 points, individual assessment),  review (presentation and submission of written document) of other group's work (pass/fail, group assessment)), individual contribution (pass/fail, individual assessment)
Phase 3 (50%, 50 points): planning project (30 points, group assessment), spatial plan map(s) (20 points, individual assessment), individual contribution (pass/fail, individual assessment)

A: 91-100 points, B: 81-90 points, C: 71-80 points, D: 61-70 points, E: 51-60 points, F: 0-50 points.

In phase 1 we evaluate:
1) overview of the planning area & aim and vision of the plan;
2) analysis of spatial mobility plans;

In phase 2 final study report we evaluate:
1) introduction and conclusions; 
2) theoretical overview; 
3) data and methods; 
4) results;
5) discussion;
6) formatting;
7) defence: final presentation and discussion.

In phase 3 planning project we evaluate:
1) substantive adequacy;
2) the use of different visualisation methods and techniques;
3) the development of the plan during the course;
4) formatting;
5) presentations and defence;
6) spatial plan map

Regarding the presentation we evaluate:
- structure of the presentation and presentation of the case,
- argumentation,
- justification of chosen viewpoints and solutions.
